data.meta_description: 690 likes, 30 comments - danpetroski on January 10, 2019: "Roald Dahl wrote in My Uncle Oswald: "Sense for me this perfume! Breathe this bouquet! Taste it! Drink it! But never try to describe it! Impossible to give an account of such a delicacy with words! To drink Roman√©e-Conti is equivalent to experiencing an orgasm at once in the mouth and in the nose." It was everything Roald said and more. Thank you @stephane.vivier.wines, this was an experience I will never forget.".
